hopobject.body: Did you go to university? supervits.com reviews San Mateo County Coroner Robert Foucrault said one of their bodies was found on the tarmac near where the plane's tail broke off. The other was found on the left side of the plane about 30 feet away from where the jetliner came to rest after it skidded down the runway. Foucrault said an autopsy will involve determining whether the second girl's death was caused by injuries suffered in the crash or "a secondary incident," and a report won't be available for two to three weeks.
